*Steps to reproduce:*
1. add the _Set Field Value from Parent_ Post Function for the _Create Issue_ transition, in the workflow applicable to sub-tasks;
2. select a Cascading Select Custom Field to be copied;
3. try to create a new sub-task and observe the error message:
!sub-task_error.png|thumbnail!

I've tested this for multiple types of Custom fields, and only manage to reproduce the error for _Project Picker_ and _Cascade Select_.

Just noticed that in an email about an issue being created, the due date is listed with a timestamp:
{quote}
Due Date:	 15/Apr/13 12:00 AM CDT
{quote}

This is inconsistent with how the field gets displayed inside JIRA.

A few moments later I got another email with an update, and that email displayed the Due Date as just a date:

{quote}
Due Date:	-15- 16 /Apr/13
{quote}
